humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states 'Lymph nodes: Sentinel lymph node. Lymph node status: Negative 0/5.' This means that out of the 5 sentinel lymph nodes assessed, none of them contained carcinoma. This matches with the definition of N0 in the new rules 10 and 11, which indicate no metastatic carcinoma in sentinel lymph nodes and regional lymph nodes, or that all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that sentinel lymph nodes 1 and 2 from the left axilla were biopsied and examined, with a total of 5 lymph nodes evaluated. No carcinoma was found in any of the lymph nodes (0/5). Therefore, the pathologic N stage for this patient is N0.
